Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Halve the @salad potatoes{350%g} lengthways and pop
onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.
Toss to coat then spread out and roast on the top shelf of your oven until
golden and cooked through, ~{25-30%minutes}, turning halfway through.

Meanwhile, trim the bottom 2cm off of the @asparagus{200%g} and discard. Cut into
thirds widthways. Zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}. Roughly chop the @dill{1}(stalks
and all). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated).

About ~{15%minutes} before the potatoes are done, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a
large #frying pan{} over medium high heat. Add the garlic and asparagus and
stir fry for ~{1%minute} then add the @rainbow chard{150%g}, season with salt and
pepper and mix well. Add the lemon zest and a splash of @water{} then cover with
a #lid{} (or some #foil{}) and cook until the asparagus and rainbow chard are
tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Lower the heat if you need to. Remove from the heat and
set aside.

While the vegetables are cooking, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in another large
frying pan over medium high heat. Season the @sea bass fillets{2} with salt and
pepper and once the oil is hot, carefully lay in the pan skin side down. Cook
for ~{2-3%minutes}, then carefully turn over and continue to cook for
~{2%minutes} on the other side.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

Once the fish is cooked, transfer to your #plates{} and cover with foil, don't
wash up your pan! Wipe out the pan (careful, it's hot!) then return the pan to
low heat. Squeeze in the lemon juice and gradually stir in the @unsalted butter{60%g}
until melted and combined. Stir in the dill and @capers{15} - this is your sauce!
Remove from the heat, taste and add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it.

Reheat the veg if necessary. Add the potatoes and vegetables to the plate with
the seabass and spoon over the buttery sauce. Cut any remaining lemon into
wedges and serve alongside for squeezing over. Enjoy!